cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and text generation. The use of recurrent neural networks with LSTM units and attention also suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the study of how the neural network decides which input words to pay attention to suggests that it could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the use of a simplified attention mechanism suggests that it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
